Created files:
- Packages/com.vtuber-system-base.core-ipc-foundation/Runtime/Core/Correlation/RequestCorrelationRegistry.cs
    Pure C# request/response correlation registry. Internal state is a
    ConcurrentDictionary<string, PendingRequest> keyed by GUID-N
    correlation ids. Per-request timeout is enforced via
    System.Threading.Timer. Public API:
        - AllocateCorrelationId() → 32-char hex GUID without dashes
          (Guid.NewGuid().ToString("N")). Cheap and thread-safe.
        - RegisterPending(correlationId, [timeout], [ct]) →
          Task<IpcResult<JsonElement>>. Adds the entry, registers a
          CancellationToken callback (if cancellable) and schedules a
          single-shot Timer for the timeout. Default timeout is taken
          from CoreIpcOptions.DefaultRequestTimeout (5s by default,
          Req 1.5 / D-8); callers may override per-call. The TCS is
          allocated with TaskCreationOptions.RunContinuationsAsynch-
          ronously so completing the source on the timer / cancel /
          transport thread does not run downstream awaiters inline.
          Disposed-state and pre-cancelled-token are handled by
          short-circuiting before insertion to avoid registering a
          callback against an already-cancelled token.
        - MatchResponse(correlationId, payload) → bool. Atomic
          TryRemove + Complete-with-Ok. Returns false for unknown ids
          (Req 9.3). On match, the timer and the cancellation
          registration are disposed so neither fires after the TCS
          is completed.
        - FailPending(correlationId, error) → bool. Atomic TryRemove
          + Complete-with-Fail. Used by transport/Bus integrations
          to surface domain errors (e.g., transport failures during
          a pending request).
        - FailAllPending(error) → int. Drains the dictionary and
          completes every pending TCS with the supplied error. Used
          internally by Dispose to deliver NotConnected to all
          in-flight callers (Req 5.x / 9.3).
        - Dispose() — Idempotent (Interlocked.Exchange guard). Marks
          the registry as disposed first, then drains. Subsequent
          RegisterPending calls return a faulted-with-NotConnected
          result without ever entering the dictionary.
    Concurrency notes:
        - All dictionary mutations go through TryAdd / TryRemove
          which are atomic on ConcurrentDictionary.
        - Timer / CancellationToken / MatchResponse / Dispose all
          race for the same correlation id; whichever wins
          TryRemove completes the TCS, the others observe the entry
          as gone and return early. TrySetResult / TrySetCanceled
          on the TCS are themselves idempotent so no double-set
          can leak through.
        - completeOnMainThread (Action<Action>?) is an optional
          injection point so that, when wired to MainThreadDispatch-
          Queue or PlayerLoop, every TCS resolution is marshalled
          onto the Unity main thread (design.md §617-§642 / Flow 2).
          Default null = inline completion; tests cover both modes.
