Implementation summary:
- Lives in namespace VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core.Correlation inside
  the existing VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core asmdef. No asmdef change
  required because Core already references the Abstractions package
  and System.Threading / System.Threading.Tasks are part of the BCL.
- Made the type public sealed (vs. the internal sketch in
  design.md §632) for test reachability and parity with
  SystemTextJsonCodec / MainThreadDispatchQueue, both of which expose
  the same access level. CoreIpc.Bus (task 2.5) will be the actual
  caller.
- Default timeout comes from CoreIpcOptions.DefaultRequestTimeout
  (5s by default, Req 1.5). Per-call override via the explicit
  timeout overload, which RequestOptions.Timeout will feed into from
  the Bus side. Negative timeouts other than Timeout.InfiniteTimeSpan
  are rejected up front.
- Cancellation completes the Task with TrySetCanceled (the .NET
  idiomatic shape) instead of an IpcResult.Fail; the registry never
  faults the Task, so aware callers can branch on
  Task.IsCanceled vs Task.Result.Success without a fault path.
- Concurrent stress test resolves 100 in-flight requests across the
  three branches (matched response / 500 ms timeout / external
  cancellation). The test asserts every Task completes within 5 s
  and that PendingRequestCount returns to zero — i.e., no leaks
  when the timer, the cancellation callback, and Dispose race for
  the same entry.

